d 'RECODE12': module to standardize 1/2-coded variables as labeled 0/1 indicators
d
d  recode12 standardizes eligible numeric variables coded 1/2 as
d labeled 0/1 indicators. The command requires the user to specify
d which source value becomes Yes/1, preserves ordinary system
d missing values, skips variables that do not satisfy the coding
d rule, supports generated-variable and replace modes, and verifies
d the resulting mapping and value range. The package includes
d documentation, an example dataset, an example do-file, and a test
d do-file. 
d
d KW: data management
d KW: binary variables
d
d Requires: Stata version 19.5
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260713
d
d Author:  Hao Ma,  NA
d Support: email shouhuoxiwang2027@@gmail.com
d
f recode12.ado
f recode12.sthlp
f recode12_test.do
f recode12_example.do
f recode12_example_data.dta
